UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407693900446
AB  - We propose an econometric estimator for a repeat-spell duration model involving fixed effects. This is applied to a simultaneous model of the size and timing of nationally-negotiated pay increases occurring in Britain during the era of incomes policy 1950–1973. We find significant impact effects of incomes policy on both the size and timing of negotiations.
